==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Conviciate
<hw>Con*vi"ci*ate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>conviciatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>conviciari</ets> to revile, fr.
<ets>convicium</ets> loud reproach.]</ety> <def>To utter reproaches; to
raise a clamor; to rail.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>conviciate</qex> instead of accusing.</q>
<rj><qau>Laud.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Convicinity</ent>⟦br⟧
